I haven't updated in a really long time, so I figured that I would give a quick lil update...

First of all, Cross Country is a KILLER!! haha...It is so painful and stressful...I am so sore from practices and meets...

I love my girls! I don't know what I would do without them!! 
-Running make you lose control!
-Floor dancing!
-G,G,G, Nite!------> HAHAHA
-There is too many to list! haha

That is really all that I feel like writing at the moment!

Sarah Renee
http://phs07-slaw15.livejournal.com/41690.html

Well, it has been a while since I have updated this thing, so I guess here goes...

First of all, the beach was wonderful! Too bad that we couldn't have stayed longer! I love the beach...I wish that I could live there! haha

Cross Country has officially started! It has been so hot and we have ran so good. We have been running at 4:30, but that's how it's gonna be at meets...

We already are on Heat Schedule. We heard on the radio today. It lasts up until Wednesday...then we get out at 12:00 for Kid's Day. I am so excited about that.

Friday there is a football scrimmage and I am excited just for the fact that it's football season. I am so excited about cheering! haha

I can't believe that my Junior year is finally here. We will be getting class rings next week and it blows my mind. I can't believe that my high school years are drawing to an end...okay, enough of the sad thoughts.

On another sad note though, the 20th I am going up to Va. Tech with Justin and his family for move in day. I know that it is going to absolutely kill me, but I know that he will be in every weekend to see me, and that will make it even more special! 

I am so glad that I have been getting to see my girls! You don't know how much I have missed them! I love 'em!!

I love all of my new school clothes that I have bought. That is my favorite part about school starting back!!

I put some photos on my photo page.

Leave me some love!
Sarah Renee

Yesterday was mine and Justin's 19th month anniversary. So, to begin the day, we shall start with that morning. First of all I went to church with Justin and then went home with him afterwards. Then we hung out for a while and ate. His family grilled out and we had hotdogs. Then we went inside and watched some t.v. and played with his cousin, Trevor. After that, we went outside for a while and then Justin decided that he wanted us to go to the top of this hill and pick some blackberries. So we did that, and it was really fun!  So then we came back home and ate so of em and watched t.v. I was laying down and ended up falling asleep for about 45 minutes. Then at 5:40, Kristina and Rach came and woke me up and told me that I needed to start getting ready. So I got ready and then Rach and Kristina, and me and Justin went and saw Charlie and the Chocolate Factory. I really liked it minus the Oompa-Lumpa's(I know that isn't spelled right so nobody laugh!! haha) Anyway, so then that ended and my mom came and picked me up. And then of course I went home.

Today I'm going to work and today I have a late night. It will be a long day! haha....After I get off work Rach and I are going to run on our own because everyone else is running at 7:00, but I don't think that I will be off in time to run at 7:00.

I am so pumped up about cheerleading camp. We leave on Thursday and then I come home and Saturday, and we leave Sunday to go on vacation. Justin is going with us, so I'm so excited! Justin is going to Tech on Wednesday and coming home Friday. He is going up there for orientation. I know that he is excited, but I am so dreading when he leaves. I just know that I won't be able to accept the fact that is 18 years old and going to college. Speaking of 18, I need to think of something to get him for his birthday. Okay, enough rambling! haha........leave me some love!

Sarah Renee
http://phs07-slaw15.livejournal.com/40748.html

Haven't had a real update in a while, so I figured that it was time! haha

Thursday we had cheerleading practice and we practiced what we're going to do for camp. It is too cute! With one practice we have it down so good. After that we stayed and ran for Cross Country...we ran to Napa and then we ran to the Town Hall and played basketball for a little while and then ran back. It was fun.

Friday I worked until about 1:30 and then I came home and got ready and picked up Rachel. Me, Rachel, Sara K., and Katelan went to Megan's aunt's house, Martha. We swam from about 3:00 til around 5:00. It was so nice cause we had pizza, chips, and cookie cake for Megz birthday. It was so fun to just get out and do something! haha

After that I met Justin at 6:15 and then we went and ate at Yamato's. After that we went back to his house and then Josh called and wanted us to go up to Joseph's house and play Poker. So we went up there until about 10:00 and then we came home. When we got there Justin discovered that he couldn't find his wallet, so we all started looking for it. Finally, he called Josh and asked if they would look for it and call back if they found it, and like one minute later they called back and had found it! haha..........When we got home we decided to watch the video ftrom Florida! I have honestly never laughed so hard in my life!!! My mom came and picked me up about 11:00.

Today I'm going to work til about 1:30 or so and then I'm going to come home and lay out in the sun for a while. Rachel is having her birthday party tonight at 6:00, so I'll have to get ready for that.

Leave me some love!

Sarah Renee

Well, it has been a while since I have updated this thing. Florida has come and gone. I absolutely LOVED it!! I wish that I could have stayed longer.

We started out at about 11:15 or so on Friday. We traveled until about 10:00 that night. Then we got up and left around 9:00 Saturday morning. We drove the rest of the way and arrived around 1:00 and then we went to Magic Kingdom. As we were starting to leave it started pourning the rain. Sunday morning we got up and went shopping because it was supposed to rain a lot that day and ended up not raining that much at all. Monday morning we got up and went to Epcot. It started raining later on in the night. We watched the fireworks at 9:00 and they were so pretty. Tuesday we went to MGM and we watched this cute little show...it was so funny! haha..We didn't get to ride Tower of Terror because they had to close it done for the day because a girl went unconcious after riding it. Wednesday we went to Cocoa Beach and then we were going to watch the shuttle launch, but they ended up not having it cause something was wrong with the fuel tank. Thursday we went to Animal Kingdom. I loved getting to see all of the cute little animals. Friday we went to Universal and I loved it!! We rode the Hulk twice and Dueling Dragons. I liked them both surprisingly enough! And they were both pretty big roller coasters. We rode some water rides too because it was so hot!!! Saturday we started out at about 9:30 or so and we drove til about 12:15 or so where we met Mike, Vicki, Kelsey Jo, Mikey, Trevor, Shirley, and Ernie and ate lunch with them. We left the mall at around 1:30 and then started back out. We stopped at around 8:00 and ate dinner at Fuddruckers and then kept on coming home. I arrived home at around 12:00 or so. I was so tired! Rachel was so glad to see me and I was so happy to be home. I really missed it.

I added some pictures to my page:
http://pg.photos.yahoo.com/ph/phs07_cheer/my_photos

Leave me some love,

Sarah Renee
http://phs07-slaw15.livejournal.com/40104.html

Well everyone, it has been a while since I have given an actual update. I am getting ready to go to work, so I figured that I would update while I waited.

First of all, I get my licenses on Thursday. I am so excited about it!! My mom said that I had to wait a week or two before she would let me drive to Norton/Wise.. but just so I get to drive! haha

Softball tourneys are this weekend at Coeburn. I hope that it isn't so hot that it's miserable!! We have practice today at 5:30 and I'm really not too sure how long that it is going to last. We have a game at home tomorrow vs. Clintwood. Clintwood, Lee County, and us are the only three teams in our District! So, that shouldn't last too long with three teams.

Work is going good. I have really put in some hours this summer! A lot more so this summer so far than last.

I am VERY excited about going to Florida with Justin and his family. We leave the 8th and come back the 16th....We are going to drive 3/4 of the way on the 8th so that on the 9th we only have about 4 hours to drive, so that we will get to do something that evening. I made a list of all the things that I will be needing to take on the trip last night, so I need to start getting a very things every time that I go to Wal-Mart. I also found out that I needed some shorts because I only have one pair of blue jean shorts. I don't ususally wear shorts, so that would be the reason! haha

On Friday I went to the BFF with Kristina, Rach, Audrey, Jessi, and Alex and then we went back to Kristina's house for her birthday sleepover. We stayed in the hot tub most of the time and it was HILARIOUS!! haha...Then Saturday, Justin went with my family to the Breaks and that was fun. We went to the pool, went to some lookouts, rode the paddleboats, and grilled out. That evening, Justin and I met his parents and we went out and ate and then we went back into his house. We got in the hot tub and it was soooo hot. It was up to 103 degrees and we had to turn it down to 95 but it only got down to 101 when we got out!

I will put some pictures on here as soon as I get them developed.

*Much love,

Sarah Renee

Could someone please tell me where this year has gone?! Honestly, it went by so fast! I can't believe that I am a Junior now. It makes me so sad to think about it. I don't even want to think about how fast these next two years are going to be. It absolutely breaks my heart to think about graduation. For instance, Lasha. We grew up together and it seems like only yesterday we were running around in diapers. Now, she is graduating on Friday and I can't believe it!

Sunday I know that I am going to be crying all day! I know that Justin is going to come home every weekend, but it's the thought. I honestly didn't think that this day would come so soon! I just wish that it didn't go by that fast.

I am so glad that summer is here. I was very ready for the break. I took my Algebra 2 semester exam and made a 100, giving me an A for the six weeks and semester. I was so proud of myself! Hopefully, I did well on my English.

Today I am going to Pikeville. I love going there! Rach has her Awards Ceremony this evening and then I am going to run. Tomorrow is the softball banquet and then Friday is graduation. Monday the Jr. Beta is going to Dollywood and Justin is giong to go with me and my mom. I love when he gets to go places with me!

Prom was so much fun! First of all, Justin came to my house at around 4:30 and we took pictures until 5:00 or so when we left to go to his house. At his house, we took more pictures and we were done with that by around 6:00. After we finished taking pictures, his mom fixed us some chicken nuggets. They were so good! We left to go to the hotel around 6:55 and arrived there around 7:05. We then took pictures until 8:00 when everyone went in. Justin and I had to take our picture at 8:05, and I really liked our picture. Prom inside was so pretty and I loved it! Then at 11:30 it was the Grand March. I was so cold outside!! I complained the whole time because I was freezing! haha...After that, we went to Justin's house and changed and then went to Katie's after prom party. We stayed there til around 2:00 or so and then we went to his house. After we got to his house, we watched Men In Black. I love that movie and I forgot how much I liked it til I watched it again. I left at like 9:00 the next morning and then I came home and we got ready to go to Norton to exchange a dress that I had bought, go to the grocery store, and then pick up Rachel. I am really sad now that it is over because it just hit me yesterday that it really was over! Now, I have graduation to cry and whine about! 

I am so glad that school is almost out. It saddens me to think that I will be a Junior, but I am so glad that summer is here and I don't have to worry about doing homework or getting up at 6:45 every morning. I love summer because I can sit at home and eat and sleep and catch up on Days! 

We have our first tournament game tomorrow vs. Powell Valley at Powell Valley. I really hope that we do really well and win. It would be wonderful!

*Much love,
Sarah Renee

Today is prom, and Justin and I will be leaving my house around 5:15 or so. Then we are going to his house to take some pictures and eat chicken nuggets.(we did that last year so we thougth that we had to do it this year! haha)After prom we are going to go to Katie's house til around 2:30 or so and then we are going to his house and my mom is going to pick me up around 6:00 or 6:30. I am so excited and ready for this! haha...I got my hair done at like 10:00 this morning and then I had a pedicure, which by the way felt so good! haha, and then I had my manicure. I loved the two of them! haha...After that we went to Mosby's and ate. I will update later and put some pictures on here soon!

*ML,
Sarah Renee

I am actually doing an update that is close the last time! haha....if that made any sense at all! Anyway, today was Award's Day at the high school. I got a Nutrition and Wellness Award and a Forensics Award. I also got my bar for my Honor P.

Then we had a game at Haysi, which wasn't bad at all. The final score was 5-2. The last time that we played them, we didn't play that well, so it was an improvement. Before the game we stopped at Hardee's and got something to eat. On the way home, we stopped and got Pizza Hut which made me very happy. 

Prom is getting so much closer. I am so excited! Friday we are going to Cheddar's to eat and then we want to go to the mall or do something else afterwards but that is still undecided. Saturday I pretty much have a busy schedule. Justin went and ordered my flowers yesterday because I had absolutely no time to go with him. With softball games everyday, there is like no time for anything really. Well, yesterday 5 of us were asked to play with 5 P.V. girls on this travelling team for about 3 weeks. I said yes and I am really excited about it!

*Sarah Renee

Well, it has definitely been a while since I have updated this thing! I have just been so busy, that I can't find the time to do this! So, I will try to remember a lot of what I have missed! haha

For starters, softball season is almost over. That makes me so sad because next softball season, I will be a Junior. I can't believe that this school year is almost over! It's like my high school career is almost over, so I am going to make the best of it! We did get yearbooks and I have almost got everyone to sign mine.

School is going good right now. Things are getting a lil wild since we are ending the school year. We have an Algebra 2 SOL soon, and that really worries me because I am finding these practice tests really hard!

Wednesday I had the stomach virus! What fun, huh?!?!? After I got to feeling better that day, we went to the Glass Slipper to pick up my prom dress! I absolutely love it and can't believe that prom is in 6 days! The dress is honestly a little too tight, so this week I really need to do some good eating and exercise. I am so excited about prom! haha

The District Track Meet was Friday night at P.V. It came a downpour!! We had to wait forever to be able to run! Kristan and I got caught in the bathroom and had to stay in there for like 30 minutes. Then it was 12:15 before we got home! I was so tired, but I got up and went to work the next morning anyway.

Yesterday I met Justin at five and we went and ate at Shannon's. Then after that we took Rachel, Kristina, Jessie, and Audrey to the JIB Pageant and we went to his house. Then I went 4wheeler riding for the very first time! Justin and I rode his uncles, and his parents rode a friends. We went several places, and I kind of had no idea where we were at one point in time. Everytime that we were close to a mud puddle, I would make Justin speed up so that it would splash all over us! Needless to say, we were a mess. At some points I was scared out of my mind! haha

After we got back, which was about an hour and 1/2 later, we changed back into clean clothes and then we watched T.V. until my mom got there. Kristina spent the night last night, and we went to bed pretty early! We were all just so tired!

Anymore it is as though I have to force myself to update this thing! For one, I never get any comments, and for two, I don't have the time! Anyway, prom was beautiful! I only stayed until 10 and then me and my mom went to Wendy's and got something to eat. After that I came home and got on the computer for a while and then I went to bed around 1:00 or so. 

Sunday morning I went to church with Justin and I was at his house until 4:00 and then we came home and I went to the batting cage and then he came with me to my Awana Banquet. After that we got home around 8:00 or so and then he left around 10:00.

Yesterday, we had a game at Coeburn and it was such a good game! The score was 3-0(us) in the bottom of the 7th. There were two outs, and then I don't remember what happened, but I do remember that they started coming back. They ended up tying it 3-3 and we had to go into 9 innings. They ended up winning 4-3. I hate that! I was so upset because to me, it hurts worse to lose that way!

Today we had softball practice in the rain and we worked on defense the whole day. I really like when we do this! We play Burton Thursday at Burton! I think that it will be a good game and I am so excited about it!

Tomorrow we have practice and then we are supposed to have a track meet at P.V. We usually go to Coeburn, but we decided to go to P.V. this week for some reason.

Prom is approaching and I am so thrilled about it. Last night, Justin told me that they couldn't get the tux that he wanted, so we have to go and order another one! I feel sorry for him because he really wanted that one too! I think that I have to get my hair done at 9:30 that morning, which is completely too early, but oh well! I will have to get my make-up done after that and then my nails done. I love to have my nails done! 

*ML,

For starters, we won our game last night which was really good...in the bottom on the 2nd inning, it started raining a little, but we kept playing. Then all of the sudden it came like a complete downpour. Both teams ran in to get in the dugouts to attempt to stay dry. Melissa, Julie Kay, and me had to go down to the baseball field with Coach Shortt to get some Diamond Dry. The bag started breaking because they were soaking wet. On the way back up the hill, Coach Shortt stopped to talk to someone and then his truck wouldn't go, so Mel, Julie, and me were screaming because we were afraid that we were going to go flying off the back of his truck. We finally made it up there though! haha

After the game, my family and Justin went to Pizza Plus and ate, and then we came home. Justin and I watched the draft thing, which was kind of cool. haha

Tonight we have a game at home against Rye Cove and then I have to run and Justin is going to run with me and then come back to my house. 

Tomorrow is prom and I am so excited even though I am not technically going. I have to do the registration and James is doing it with me. About 9:30 or 10:00 Justin is going to pick me up and then he wants me to go to his house. I just love him to death!!

Since I have updated this thing, we have played Norton and Wise and we won against Norton(very good game!) and we lost 5-2 to Wise.  Keisha hurt her knee and I was really worried about her, but she informed me on Friday that she is alright and could possibly be playing on Monday against Appy.

It has been a few days since I have updated this thing! haha

Tuesday we had a softball game against Clintwood and almost lost to them! They have improved so much since last year!  We came out of it and won 6-3.  Our defense looked awesome! I know that some of it was my fault because my pitching really sucked that night!

Wednesday I didn't go to softball practice because we had our first Track Meet! I was ready for it, but my time for the 2-mile was HORRIBLE! I don't even want to go there with that one, and I'm praying that it drops....A LOT! 

Thursday we had a game against Coeburn at home.  They have really improved since last year as well.  We lost that one 12-1. We really need to start hitting the ball better as a team. Defense is still really strong for us right now.  After that I had Justin to run with me at the track and then we picked up our order from Pizza Plus...which was wrong, but that's okay.haha
